# Cursor Rules: Model Self-Identification (Experimental)

# Always attempt to identify the model before answering
Before answering any user request, you must:

1. State the exact model name and version you are running.
2. If you are unsure, explicitly say "Model unknown".
3. Do not guess or fabricate a model name.
4. Keep this statement to one short line.

# Then proceed with the normal answer.

# Example format:
# Model: GPT-5.3
# <actual answer>

# If the system prevents you from knowing the model,
# you must say:
# Model: unknown

# Do not skip this step under any circumstances.